18 The bill does the following:
19 1. It authorizes the Manufactured Housing Board to petition the Office of the Attorney
20 General to investigate a violation of, and enforce the provisions of, in the Maine Revised
21 Statutes, Title 10, chapter 953;
22 2. It amends the provisions in Title 10, chapter 953, that require the owner of a
23 manufactured housing community proposing to raise the lot rent or fees in the community
24 to participate in mediation with the owners of the community impacted by a proposed lot
25 rent or fee increase under certain circumstances. It requires the community owner to notify
26 the homeowners of the community of the percent change in the Consumer Price Index for
27 the Northeast Region during the 12-month period prior to the proposed lot rent or fee
28 increase. It clarifies that only the homeowners impacted by the proposed increase may
29 request the community owner participate in mediation and that a request is permitted only
30 if the proposed lot rent or fee increase is a percentage increase higher than the Consumer
31 Price Index percent increase provided in the notice.
32 3. It clarifies that for purposes of Title 9-A, Article 9, "real estate" includes
33 manufactured housing or tiny homes regardless of whether title to the real property to which
34 the housing or home is affixed is owned by the owner of the housing or home.
35 4. It clarifies for purposes of the Maine Secure and Fair Enforcement for Mortgage
36 Licensing Act of 2009, that the term "dwelling" includes manufactured housing or tiny
37 homes regardless of whether title to the real property to which the housing or home is
38 affixed is owned by the owner of the housing or home.
39 5. It allows the owner of manufactured housing or a tiny home to request the Secretary
40 of State to cancel the certificate of title for the manufactured housing or tiny home as long
41 as the owner files certain documents in the registry of deeds in the county where the
42 manufactured housing or tiny home is located. Completion of the actions by the owner and
